Response ID: resp_3110
Response Text: ACME needs to partner and fund these smaller organizations that are doing the work already it doesn't need to be a wheel that is reinvented. Also there needs to be diversity in the leadership that is sourcing these opportunities not just white people with money and access to spaces. Austin was built on this concept on being weird but a lot of what is funded and broadcasted for entertainment has been trendy we need to involve the smaller creatives creating variety shows and creating spaces for new artists. Gothess Jasmine, Natalie Lepore, Monster Mash, Sir Beau Elliot Beauregard, What's in The Mirror, Queer Black Women Alliance, Pride in Black, allgo, Sunday Sessions, House of Von Dutch, House of Lepore, ATC Choclit, Local Queer, Asian Family Support Services of Austin and Diamond Davenport. These are just some of the organizers and organizations really providing spaces for minority artists, cultural heritage and accessible spaces to exist.

